dcterms:creator: T. Ishigami
T. Homma
dcterms:description: The Ishigami function is commonly used for benchmarking global sensitivity analyses and uncertainty quantification. It is a three-dimensional function defined by a specific analytic expression involving sine functions.
dcterms:title: Ishigami function

dcterms:creator: H. H. Rosenbrock
dcterms:description: The Rosenbrock function is a non-convex function widely used in optimization benchmarks. It is defined as a sum of squares of non-linear functions of its variables.
dcterms:title: Rosenbrock function

dcterms:creator: P. H. Cook
M. A. McDonald
M. C. P. Firmin
dcterms:description: The RAE2822 airfoil dataset includes pressure distributions, boundary layer, and wake measurements for a supercritical airfoil, which is a standard test case for turbulence modeling validation in transonic regimes.
dcterms:title: RAE2822 airfoil
